FBIS4-46353 "jptot024__l94030" JPRS-TOT-94-024-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 5 June 1994 LATIN AMERICA COLOMBIA Bomb Kills Two in Arauca; Police Blame Rebels Bomb Kills Two in Arauca; Police Blame Rebels PA0506144794 Paris AFP in Spanish 1355 GMT 5 Jun 94 PA0506144794 Paris AFP Spanish BFN [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 5 Jun (AFP) -- A dynamite bomb of moderate force killed two people when it exploded. The two people were carrying the bomb this Sunday in downtown Arauca, capital of the eastern department bearing the same name, located near the border with Venezuela, 350 km east of Santa Fe de Bogota, the police have informed. The victims, Elizabeth Medina and William Montilla, were riding a motorcycle in downtown Arauca when the bomb went off. The Arauca police are investigating the incident and said the guerrillas are to blame for the bloody incident, considering the upcoming 19 June presidential elections, in which the successor of President Cesar Gaviria for the 1994-1998 period will be chosen.
